From Matt Austern Subject Re The state of justice In article senator John F Carr writes I recommend the book Adams v Texas the story of a man Adams who was sentenced to death for a crime he didn't Most of the book is the story of the long appeals process and the problems and delays caused by not being able to introduce new evidence in certain And I recommend the movie The Thin Blue Line which is about the same Not as much legal detail but still an excellent It shows how very easy it is to come up with seemingly conclusive evidence against someone whom you think is Matthew Austern Maybe we can eventually make language a complete impediment to